posts.name: Chadfrom7226
NewtonCrosby
posts.cooked:
You can keep your binding to whileTrue() as you have it.

Just add an end() method to your command (or a finallyDo() if you’re using compositions) where you set the motors to 0.

Then while the trigger is high, the motors are set to on.  When whileTrue() becomes false (i.e. the button is released) the scheduler will interrupt the running command and call the end() method of the command.
